      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "@id": "http://dbpedia.org/resource/Blitzscaling",
    "@type": [
      "http://schema.org/Book"
    ],
    "http://schema.org/author": [
      {
        "@id": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/chrisyeh/#this"
      },
      {
        "@id": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/reidhoffman/#this"
      }
    ],
    "http://schema.org/name": [
      {
        "@language": "en",
        "@value": "Blitzscaling"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "@id": "https://hardcoresoftware.learningbyshipping.com/p/228-deepseek-has-been-inevitable#q9",
    "@type": [
      "http://schema.org/Question"
    ],
    "http://schema.org/acceptedAnswer": [
      {
        "@id": "https://hardcoresoftware.learningbyshipping.com/p/228-deepseek-has-been-inevitable#a9"
      }
    ],
    "http://schema.org/isPartOf": [
      {
        "@id": "https://hardcoresoftware.learningbyshipping.com/p/228-deepseek-has-been-inevitable#faqSection"
      }
    ],
    "http://schema.org/name": [
      {
        "@language": "en",
        "@value": "Why couldn't US hyperscalers see the disruption coming?"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "@id": "https://hardcoresoftware.learningbyshipping.com/p/228-deepseek-has-been-inevitable#a8",
    "@type": [
      "http://schema.org/Answer"
    ],
    "http://schema.org/text": [
      {
        "@language": "en",
        "@value": "As the predictable 'scale-out' commoditization phase that follows every 'scale-up' technology cycle — mainframe to mini to micro to mobile, big iron to distributed computing to internet — with hyperscalers missing it because massive capex aligned with their existing cloud infrastructure rather than because it was the smartest path."
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "@id": "https://hardcoresoftware.learningbyshipping.com/p/228-deepseek-has-been-inevitable#a10",
    "@type": [
      "http://schema.org/Answer"
    ],
    "http://schema.org/text": [
      {
        "@language": "en",
        "@value": "A tiny recursive model that solves logic problems without massive-scale training, winning a $50,000 prize and showing that genuinely efficient alternatives to brute-force scaling exist."
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "@id": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/reidhoffman/#this",
    "@type": [
      "http://schema.org/Person"
    ],
    "http://schema.org/name": [
      {
        "@language": "en",
        "@value": "Reid Hoffman"
      }
    ],
    "http://schema.org/url": [
      {
        "@id": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/reidhoffman/"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "@id": "https://hardcoresoftware.learningbyshipping.com/p/228-deepseek-has-been-inevitable#a11",
    "@type": [
      "http://schema.org/Answer"
    ],
    "http://schema.org/text": [
      {
        "@language": "en",
        "@value": "Hoffman describes blitzscaling as 'assembling a plane while falling.' Applied to AI, vague 'compute multiplier' efficiency claims mean the trillion-dollar bet cannot retrofit efficiency later if capital access tightens — the bubble-risk scenario."
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "@id": "https://hardcoresoftware.learningbyshipping.com/p/228-deepseek-has-been-inevitable#q2",
    "@type": [
      "http://schema.org/Question"
    ],
    "http://schema.org/acceptedAnswer": [
      {
        "@id": "https://hardcoresoftware.learningbyshipping.com/p/228-deepseek-has-been-inevitable#a2"
      }
    ],
    "http://schema.org/isPartOf": [
