  {
    "@id": "https://hardcoresoftware.learningbyshipping.com/p/228-deepseek-has-been-inevitable#a1",
    "@type": [
      "http://schema.org/Answer"
    ],
    "http://schema.org/text": [
      {
        "@language": "en",
        "@value": "Blitzscaling, from Reid Hoffman and Chris Yeh's book, prioritizes speed of growth over operational efficiency on the assumption efficiency can be retrofitted after scale is captured. Ilya Sutskever's framing of brute-force compute scaling as 'low-risk' mirrors this logic applied to model training."
      }
    ]
  }
